\begin_layout Section
Foil Thickness
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The thickness of the foil was determined by making many micrometer measurements
 of foil from an adjacent portion of the same roll.
 Touching the foil, particularly with a hard/sharp-cornered object like
 a micrometer, can easily damage the foil by denting it.
 Even a piece of dust, compressed between a micrometer jaw and the foil,
 can be sufficient to dimple the foil and increase its effective thickness.
 For this reason, we have not directly measured the actual foil's thickness.
 If the foil thickness measurement were to become of increased concern,
 we could destructively test it.
\end_layout

