\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With the clock rates matched, we must then align the zeroes of each clock
 at the start of each run.
 The clocks were manually observed to be synchronous with sub-second precision
 in almost every run.
 In a few cases, they were observed to be asynchronous with as much as a
 25
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

s offset.
 To be conservative, we assume that no run is synchronized to better than
 25
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

s.
 Dropping 50
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

s per step, or 100
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

s per period, is a brutal but acceptable step, as the attractor-motion period
