 should be rechecked and confirmed by others.
 The only reasons to stop hunting for both greater sensitivity and experimental
 certainty are if the level of measurement precision substantially exceeds
 theoretical prediction or if no major experimental improvements are feasible.
 In the case of short-range gravity, the former is unlikely to happen in
 our lifetime, and the latter is precluded by our short list of easy experimenta
